definitions.definition: The son of Abraham and Sarah , father of Esau and Jacob , from whom the Hebrew people trace their descent.
A male given name from Hebrew .
A surname originating as a patronymic .
A local government area in central Queensland , Australia , named after the Isaac River ; in full, Isaac Region .
